<paragraph blockId="62.[163,1071,519,718]" pageId="62" pageNumber="445">R e c o g n i t i o n: Body all black and the gaster with a metallic shine. The propodeal enclosure is transversely striate and glabrous, the pronotal collar and the scutum are distinctly transversely striate. Additionally, the supra-antennal lamellate projection is slightly developed, the mesothoracic venter is not prominent anteriorly and the episternal sulcusis extending to the anteroventral margin of the pleuron.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="62.[163,1072,733,784]" pageId="62" pageNumber="445">
<taxonomicName box="[163,366,733,754]" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Ammophila" kingdom="Plantae" order="Poales" pageId="62" pageNumber="445" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="honorei">
<emphasis box="[163,366,733,754]" italics="true" pageId="62" pageNumber="445">Ammophila honorei</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
resembles to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="F. SMITH" authorityYear="1856" box="[511,639,733,755]" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Ammophila" kingdom="Plantae" order="Poales" pageId="62" pageNumber="445" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="terminata">
<emphasis box="[511,639,733,755]" italics="true" pageId="62" pageNumber="445">A. terminata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and differs only in having a black gaster. Maybe it is the black form of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="F. SMITH" authorityYear="1856" box="[465,591,763,784]" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Ammophila" kingdom="Plantae" order="Poales" pageId="62" pageNumber="445" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="terminata">
<emphasis box="[465,591,763,784]" italics="true" pageId="62" pageNumber="445">A. terminata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="62.[163,1070,799,938]" pageId="62" pageNumber="445">D e s c r i p t i o n: Body all black, gaster with metallic shine. Propodeal enclosure transversely striate and glabrous, pronotal collar and scutum distinctly transversely striate. Scutellum longitudinally striate, supra-antennal lamellate projection slightly developed. Mesothoracic venter not prominent anteriorly, episternal sulcus extending to anteroventral margin of pleuron, arolia well developed and claws without basal tooth.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="62.[163,1070,954,1122]" pageId="62" pageNumber="445">
<specimenCount box="[163,184,960,981]" pageId="62" pageNumber="445" type="female">♀</specimenCount>
: 
<quantity box="[199,327,954,976]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.725" metricValueMax="1.95" metricValueMin="1.5" pageId="62" pageNumber="445" unit="mm" value="17.25" valueMax="19.5" valueMin="15.0">15-19.5 mm</quantity>
. Clypeus, frons, pronotal lobe, spots on propodeum posterolaterally and dorsal surface of mid- and hindcoxa covered with appressed silvery setae; erect setae on head and prothorax dark-brown, on mesothorax and propodeum whitish. Clypeus slightly elongate, with truncate median lobe, disk distinctly convex (
<figureCitation box="[819,914,1042,1064]" captionStart="Figs 85-109" captionStartId="136.[163,203,1391,1411]" captionTargetBox="[195,1050,236,1368]" captionTargetId="figure-1@136.[163,1071,204,1371]" captionTargetPageId="136" captionText="Figs 85-109: clypeus of female in lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5341152" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5341152/files/figure.png" pageId="62" pageNumber="445">Fig. 104</figureCitation>
). Mesopleuron distinctly transversely striate. Flagellomere I: II=1.9; length of petiole = hindtarsomeres I+0.75×II to I+II.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="62.[163,1071,1137,1335]" pageId="62" pageNumber="445">
3: 
<quantity box="[206,288,1137,1159]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.8" pageId="62" pageNumber="445" unit="mm" value="18.0">18 mm</quantity>
. Clypeus, frons, broad patch along mesopleural suture, pronotal lobe, propodeal hindface from hindcoxa to propodeal dorsum and mid- and hindcoxa covered with appressed silvery setae; erect setae on head and prothorax brown, on mesothotax and propodeum laterally white. Clypeus slightly elongate (
<figureCitation box="[766,856,1225,1247]" captionStart="Figs 240-252" captionStartId="150.[163,203,1393,1413]" captionTargetBox="[171,1069,219,1373]" captionTargetId="figure-1@150.[163,1070,204,1373]" captionTargetPageId="150" captionText="Figs 240-252: male clypeus." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5341181" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5341181/files/figure.png" pageId="62" pageNumber="445">Fig. 246</figureCitation>
), clypeal disk nearly flat (
<figureCitation box="[213,306,1255,1277]" captionStart="Figs 357-373" captionStartId="158.[163,203,1234,1254]" captionTargetBox="[163,1065,241,1187]" captionTargetId="figure-1@158.[163,1070,204,1214]" captionTargetPageId="158" captionText="Figs 357-373: male clypeus in lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5341197" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5341197/files/figure.png" pageId="62" pageNumber="445">Fig. 365</figureCitation>
). Mesopleuron dull, slightly transversely striate. Pronotal collar laterally: 
<figureCitation box="[163,250,1284,1306]" captionStart="Figs 292-306" captionStartId="154.[163,203,1507,1527]" captionTargetBox="[177,1055,225,1482]" captionTargetId="figure-1@154.[163,1070,204,1487]" captionTargetPageId="154" captionText="Figs 292-306: pronotal collar of male in lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5341189" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5341189/files/figure.png" pageId="62" pageNumber="445">Fig. 301</figureCitation>
; gonostyle laterally: 
<figureCitation box="[462,550,1284,1306]" captionStart="Figs 398-413" captionStartId="161.[163,203,1487,1507]" captionTargetBox="[165,1070,230,1453]" captionTargetId="figure-1@161.[163,1070,204,1467]" captionTargetPageId="161" captionText="Figs 398-413: male genitalia: gonostyle in lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5341203" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5341203/files/figure.png" pageId="62" pageNumber="445">Fig. 413</figureCitation>
; penis valve laterally: 
<figureCitation box="[778,865,1284,1306]" captionStart="Figs 491-508" captionStartId="167.[163,203,1481,1501]" captionTargetBox="[170,1035,220,1461]" captionTargetId="figure-1@167.[163,1070,204,1461]" captionTargetPageId="167" captionText="Figs 491-508: male genitalia: penis valve in lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5341216" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5341216/files/figure.png" pageId="62" pageNumber="445">Fig. 500</figureCitation>
, ventrally: 
<figureCitation box="[979,1067,1284,1306]" captionStart="Figs 546-562" captionStartId="170.[163,203,1352,1372]" captionTargetBox="[163,1069,224,1315]" captionTargetId="figure-1@170.[163,1070,204,1332]" captionTargetPageId="170" captionText="Figs 546-562: male genitalia: penis valve in ventral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5341222" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5341222/files/figure.png" pageId="62" pageNumber="445">Fig. 556</figureCitation>
